            <abstract>
                <p>Magic prayer against <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቍር፡</foreign>, which, according to 
                    <bibl><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1978BritishLibrary"/><citedRange unit="page">150</citedRange></bibl>, is a  prayer 
                    'against a cold', i.e. a short-term inflammation of the airways or a viral infectious disease. However, there is no attestation 
                    of <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቍር፡</foreign> referring to a disease. From the beginning of the prayer alone, it could be
                    intended to protect against the pain by weather.</p>
